cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper focuses on spiking neural networks, which are a type of artificial neural network. This is a sub-category of cs.NE.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper evaluates the proposed methods on image classification datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, and CIFAR-100. This suggests that the paper is related to computer vision and pattern recognition, which is a sub-category of cs.CV.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep spiking neural network model and a novel hybrid neural coding scheme, which are related to machine learning. This is a sub-category of cs.LG.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method for improving the efficiency and accuracy of spiking neural networks, which are a type of artificial intelligence. This is a sub-category of cs.AI.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the transmission of information between neurons in spiking neural networks, which can be considered a control problem. This is a sub-category of cs.SY.
